11/11/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- A witness in the trial against former Kosovo Liberation Army commanders and former Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj was arrested on Friday (November 9th) for contempt of court. Avni Krasniqi was charged with contempt after he did not appear to testify against Haradinaj and two other convicts, charged with crimes against Serbs, Romas and Albanians in Kosovo between March 1st and September 30th 1998. The Hague war crimes tribunal said that throughout the trial against Haradinaj it has seen signs of witness intimidation. (RTS, B92- 10/11/07; AP, Reuters - 09/11/07)
